<br>
Hundreds of years ago, Europe &amp; America were much greener/ wilder places than (sadly) they are today … vast acres of forests still remained, even here in the UK.<br>
<br>
The Church feared this … all this wilderness represented something untamed &amp; (seemingly) untameable , something threatening and beyond control.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Clerics (I’m talking here about mainstream, Roman, Dominican clerics) tended to live slightly removed from their ‘flocks’, and from the realities of everyday life.  Christian clerics who tried to live more humbly &amp; in-touch with people (such as the Franciscans or other ‘roaming’ clerics)  ended up suffering persecution. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In this climate, any person who appeared to have any knowledge/ understanding of the rythms of ‘nature’ – who could read the seasons, understand animal husbandry, have knowledge of cures/ remedies etc – would automatically fall under suspicion.<br>
<br>
Basically, nature was regarded (by the Roman Church) as essentially malevolent, even evil.<br>
<br>
A fascinating illustration of this: has anyone heard of the pagan deity known as ‘Pan’??<br>
<br>
Pan represented nature &amp; (more subtly) sexuality: he was half-goat, half-human, had horns and hoves etc, (sound familiar?).  He was not a malevolent deity, and had no pagan associations with ‘evil’, in any sense.<br>
<br>
However (the theory goes) the Christian Church, fearful of nature (and, arguably, also of sexuality) took the characteristics of Pan and used them to charcterise and depict Satan: they – quite literally – demonised him! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A couple of interesting links about Pan:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.mc.maricopa.edu/users/shoemaker/StudentPapers/pan.html">www.mc.maricopa.edu/users...s/pan.html</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
